1. Flexbox:

Use for one-dimensional layouts (rows or columns).
Ideal for navigation bars, lists, and flexible box containers.
Best for aligning items along a single axis.


CSS Grid:

Use for two-dimensional layouts (rows and columns).
Ideal for complex grid-based designs and overall page structures.
Best for precise control over the placement of items in both dimensions.
Consider Both:

They can be used together for more sophisticated and responsive layouts.
Flexbox within CSS Grid for nested structures.
